Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 3, Miami (OH) 0

The Wildcats dominate on both ends in their NCAA Tournament debut, and will face the winner of the Iowa-Louisville matchup in the quarters on Sunday afternoon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern snuffs out a Miami corner. Under seven minutes to play, and this is pretty much over.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The call gets overturned? No foul

Name: Inside NU
Content: Some beautiful ball movement from the 'Cats before Wadas gets tripped inside the circle. Play is under review.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two more corners for NU, two saves. The 'Cats have seven shots on goal now.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF THIRD: NU 3, Miami 0
For the second time in three contests, Northwestern breaks the game open with a third-quarter outburst. Goals from Bent-Cole and Tromp have all but put this one away.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Olivia Bent-Cole scored. 3-0. Bump.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The selection committee may not think so, but Northwestern sure looked like the best team in the land on Friday afternoon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miami earns a corner of its own on the other end, but the backhand shot from Claudia Negrete Garcia is wide. Under a minute left in the third quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Tromp, on cue! It’s 2-zip.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miami starting to generate some momentum in transition, but a takeaway from Northwestern leads to another corner. Another chance to double the lead

Name: Inside NU
Content: Miami's first shot of the day is knocked away by Annabel Skubisz!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Some really nice stick work by Miami down the sideline, and the RedHawks draw a corner. Their first huge scoring opportunity of the day.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Tromp zings it.... off the crossbar. It sounded like the back of the net rang, that's how hard the shot was. So close to doubling the lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It took three minutes for Northwestern to earn its first corner of the second half. Shot is saved, but Northwestern earns another.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Second half is underway.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALFTIME: Northwestern 1, Miami (OH) (total shots) 0

The Wildcats absolutely dominated possession in the first half, and are 30 minutes away from a rematch with either Iowa or Louisville in the quarters.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lindsey Frank with a takeaway in Miami's end, and she almost got a clean look at the goal, but her shot is blocked. Under five minutes to go in the first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: This press, as it has been all year, is absolutely stifling. We are more than 21 minutes in, and Miami has not taken a single shot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Another corner for Northwestern, but this time the ensuing shot goes wide.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF FIRST: Northwestern 1, Miami (OH) 0
It was quiet on both sides to start, but the 'Cats gradually got some pressure on the RedHawks' side of the field, and it paid off in Wadas' goal.

Name: Inside NU
Content: First corner for Northwestern with just under a minute to go, and it finds the back of the net! It's Lauren Wadas to put the 'Cats up 1-0!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Eleven minutes in, and Alia Marshall takes the first shot of the game. It deflects upward and bounces toward the side of the net.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Through five minutes, no shots from either team. Some sloppy passing on both sides, as the ball's stayed in the midfield for the most part.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We're off!

Name: Inside NU
Content: No lineup changes from the Big Ten Tournament Final: Skubisz, Wadas, Bent-Cole, Halsey, Tromp, Hinke, Relford, Katie Jones, Lauren Hunter, Marshall, Frank

Name: Inside NU
Content: Live from Lakeside Field, where the ‘Cats begin their postseason quest for a third straight trip to the title game (and second championship in three years) against Miami Ohio! Stay tuned for live tweets and some written coverage!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Which happens this Saturday: Northwestern snap a 14-game road skid, or the Wildcats drop two straight for the first time all year? ,  and  try to make sense of it (and the Wrigley game) on Pound the Talk.

Content: Next up in Olympic sports previews: the 2023-24 wrestling squad.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown**

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown: "A lot of great things happened tonight."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown notes that Crystal Wang and Mercy Ademusayo will play big roles for the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKeown on Walsh: "She's a big piece if we're going to be successful. We gotta keep her out of foul trouble."

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKewon on UIC's 18-0 run: "Not what you game plan. We came out in complete control, but I thought we played too fast and played into their hands."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKewon: "A tale of two halves. I really liked the way we played in overtime. There are a lot of things we need to work on."

He then gives a shoutout to  for getting into the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McKewon now at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley: "We have a chip on our shoulder. Last year was rough. We have nothing to lose. We're coming for it all."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott on Lau: " I'm so proud of her. She's a natural leader."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott on turnovers: "A lot of it is our own fault. A lot of unforced errors."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott on the halftime message: "You don't have to win the third quarter, you just have to fight back."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mott: "My mom told me to get 20 [rebounds]."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley: "It was fun. I have nothing else to say really."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley and Mott at the podium

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern rallies and defeats UIC 92-84 in overtime to open the 2023-2024 season. NU trailed by as much as 19.

Melannie Daley led the 'Cats with 27 points, and Paige Mott added 20 rebounds

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver is fouled and will shoot two.

This one is over.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Referees rule UIC's ball, but the Flames toss it out of bounds with 19.5 seconds to play.

'Cats will take over.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver's three is no good, but the referees will take a look at who touched it last.

90-84 NU with 27.2 seconds left in overtime.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Timeout on the floor for an injured player.

NU leading 86-80 with 1:40 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Daley has 27 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
High arcing shot from Daley find the bottom of the basket to expand Northwestern’s lead to six with three minutes left in overtime.

Timeout UIC.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver sinks a three to open the overtime period.

78-75 Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lau's shot rolls around and off the rim as the buzzer sounds.

Free basketball at Welsh-Ryan.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The first free throw is no good, but the second one is.

75-75 with 17.2 seconds left. Timeout NU.

 'Cats will have the final shot of regulation.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Walsh picks up her fifth foul with 17.2 seconds to go.

Her night is done. UIC to shoot two.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Tough finish by UIC to retake the lead, but Mott responded on the other end.

Back-and-forth we go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
PAIGE MOTT!!

She grabs her 17th board of the game and finishes through contact for an and-one.

NU back ahead 73-72 with less than a minute.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bad pass from Lau, and the Flames capitalize.

72-70 UIC with 90 seconds remaining. Timeout NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lau lays it in, and we are all tied up.

70-70 with less than two minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Walsh for three!

NU only down by two with less than three to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Daley cannot convert the and-one opportunity, and UIC lays it in on the other end.

McKewon calls a full timeout. 70-65 UIC with 3:29 remaining.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Flames connect from beyond the arc to retake the lead.

On the other side of the floor, Weaver draws a foul and will shoot two.

64-61 UIC with 4:30 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
All tied up after UIC splits a pair of free throws.

61-61 halfway through the fourth quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Caileigh Walsh picks up her fourth foul.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Both teams are trading blows here to open the fourth quarter.

NU clinging to a 61-59 lead with seven minutes left in the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern leads UIC 57-52 after three quarters.

'Cats outscored the Flames 27-8 in the quarter, holding UIC scoreless for the final four minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern is shooting 67% in the second half.

Offensive. Juggernaut.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lau picks up her third foul with 1:26 left in the third quarter.

Coach McKewon is leaving her out on the floor.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mott lays it in, and the 'Cats lead for the first time since it was 16-10.

NU is on a 9-0 run.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
MELANNIE DALEY AND-ONE!!

She hits a tough jumper through contact and converts from the charity stripe.

NU down 52-51.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lau drills a three, but UIC capitalizes on a turnover to hold its lead at 8.

NU still behind 52-44 with 3:40 left to play in the third quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Four minutes into the half, NU is on a 7-0 run to cut the deficit to 10.

Time out UIC.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Trotter hits her fourth triple of the game to open up the second half.

She can flat-out shoot.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
NU is able to connect on its final three field goals of the half but finds itself facing a sizable deficit heading into the locker room.

Flames lead 44-30 after two quarters.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Trotter is doing whatever she wants on the floor, going on a 6-0 run of her own.

UIC is outscoring the 'Cats 20-7 in the second quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
15 combined turnovers so far.

Both teams trying to work out the early season hiccups.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Scramble for the ball ends up with Weaver, and she lays it in.

Timeout UIC.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Caileigh Walsh and-one!

The junior converts the three-point play to cut it to single digits.

30-21 UIC with five minutes left in the half.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Paige Mott scores Northwestern’s first points of the second quarter.

Wildcats still trail by double digits.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
UIC on a 7-0 run to start the quarter, and Joe McKewon calls a timeout.

Wildcats are down 26-16.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
A half-court heave from Dais'Ja Trotter banks off the glass and falls in to cap off a UIC 9-0 run to close out the first quarter.

'Cats trail 19-16.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Daley finds the bottom of the net,  and Walsh lays one in on the next possession.

'Cats starting to heat up.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Another Flames' triple evens the game at 8.

After starting 3-3 from the field, the Wildcats are one for their last eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver drops the pass, and UIC drills a three.

8-5 NU halfway through the quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weaver draws the charge but bricks the layup on the other end.

6-2 'Cats two minutes into the contest.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Tonight's starters for the 'Cats

G: Caroline Lau
G: Hailey Weaver
G: Melannie Daley
F: Caileigh Walsh
F: Paige Mott

Name: Inside NU
Content: Skubisz on staying dialed in on the moment: "Every game could be your last. The end doesn't matter if you can't get there."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Fuchs on Bent-Cole's speed: "Speed kills. We have Liv up front, who as a ton of it, and then Alia, Lindsey on the outside. And when Lauren Wadas gets going, she's really quick.

"Your skill has to match your speed. And certainly, Liv epitomizes her skill."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Fuchs called this Northwestern team the most consistent she's coached in 15 years.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Skubisz on the difference between the mentality this year and 2021/2022: "We're not worried about the expectations that have been set for us, we're worried about meeting our own standards that we set at the beginning of the season."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Tracey Fuchs notes that getting to see Miami (OH) last spring has helped the 'Cats getting to know the RedHawks' style of play.

On how they've grown since then: "We're so much more balanced across every line."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Annabel Skubisz on Northwestern field hockey getting the No. 2 seed: "I don't want to say slighted, but it pushes us to keep proving ourselves. We've got to show the country that we deserve the No. 1 seed."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins mentioned "breakdowns," some of them in communication, as to why the defense faltered against Binghamton.

"It takes time to build that. I'm confident, the more those guys play, the better we'll get on that end."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins said that tomorrow's game against Dayton has a "big-game feel" and that Northwestern is expecting a sellout.

Stressed that there's "excitement" among players in playing the Flyers, who are the A10 preseason favorites.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Chris Collins said that Nick Martinelli's minutes limit isn't something that the team isn't worried about "long term," but that NU is still conscious of his injury.

"We've got to look at the long term. He's doing well."

Name: Inside NU
Content: If the Wildcats want to curtail their two-game streak against Wisconsin, they’ll need to execute in these areas.

Content:
Four of Northwestern fencing’s eight bouts to start the season:

About as tough an opening weekend as you’ll find in all of college sports.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Something about purple teams and No. 4 Michigan State…

Name: Inside NU
Content: That ends tonight's media availability.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie on preparing for Dayton: "We've just got to take it one day at a time."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on fan support tonight: "If more was here, it would've been even more fun. It got really loud in there, for how many people were in there."

Said it was "awesome" to have turnout tonight.

"Without them there tonight, I think that game could go differently."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on Barnhizer playing point: "Brooks is a walking mismatch. He brings a physicality on the defensive end. He's super strong. He's able to find people off the dribble."

Said he's "never stopped working" since he arrived.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg on Preston, a fellow transfer: "Super aggressive. He left it all on the court. Unmatched effort on the bench. That's exactly what we need."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg on playing five guards: "The bigs have to play on the perimeter. At the end of the day, it just comes down to communication."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on fixing turnovers: "I think I was just playing a little fast in the beginning. As an older guy, it kind of just slowed down."

Said that he needs to be "more poised" in attacking.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Langborg on his first game at Welsh-Ryan Arena: "I wouldn't say jitters. Just excitement. It was so much fun, to come out of it with a win. We didn't get off to the start we wanted."

Noted that he's not used to playing in front of many students.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on Jordan Clayton: "I was really impressed by Jordan. He just bought in from the jump. He was one of the best guards on the defensive end tonight. Without his contribution, we don't win that game tonight."

Called his minutes "17 strong minutes."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Langborg: "We're very connected."

Said that Buie was "willing" the team with messages.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie on tonight's game: "I just think that our defense, when we first came out, we didn't start off with great offense. They got off to a hot start. That was something that we focused on at halftime."

Called the better defense a "standard" with the need to "buy in" on D.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie and Ryan Langborg now speaking.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's all from Collins from the opener.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "We would not have won if we were not about the right things tonight."

Praised "grit" and "toughness."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on maintaining elements from last year to now: "I have not talked about last year with these guys at all. It's all been about this group. We know we've got to get better. New roles. Every team is different. We're all about now, and not looking back."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on adjusting to Symir Torrence: "We actually recruited him a little bit when he was in high school. He's a really good player. Forcing him into eight turnovers was really big."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins' message to students: "We need you Friday night. They're going to try to bring the red in the building."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on the Dayton matchup: "It's the reason why we scheduled the game. We specifically wanted to play a high-level team early to see where we're at."

Called the Flyers "terrific."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Luke Hunger not playing: "Just kind of matchup. I want him to stay ready."

Said that the team had to play a smaller lineup because of Binghamton utilizing more guards.

"Sometimes in these non-league games, it's a little bit harder with these bigger guys."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Justin Mullins: "He's an athlete. He's a young player. He was able to get his feet wet a little bit."

Said that he stressed that every player will be needed in his postgame message.

"All these guys who are young players just got to keep working."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on assists/turnovers regressing: "I thought Boo had a couple sloppy ones he's got to clean up. My goal coming into the game, I try for us to be 2-to-1, or as close to that as possible."

Said that 10 turnovers is a "magic number."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on Barnhizer's rebounding: "We need it. As we play some of the teams, there will be times when we'll be a little bit undersized. I think Brooks is going to be a guy. Workman-like on the glass. Everyone has to chip in."

Noted a "gang rebound" mentality.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on Clayton's debut/role: "I think it was game-by-game. I'm trying to win the game. Tonight, I felt Jordan's defense. He was very solid. He was keeping the ball in front of him. He wasn't turning the ball over. I thought we needed him on the floor."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins said that Langborg and Clayton can be ball-handlers when Buie is out.

Called Barnhizer a "matchup issue" as the "power forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins said that the team wants Buie/Barnhizer/Langborg/Berry to be the "focus" of the offense. Stressed foul trouble as not allowing Berry to find a rhythm.

"It's up to me to get those guys shots."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on Clayton: "For him to come in as a freshman and give us that dirty work, was pretty impressive."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on being better in the fastbreak: "I think we have to be more opportunistic."

Said the team needs to do better taking advantage of turnovers.

"I feel like we have more offensive firepower than we had a year ago."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "We have a lot to learn. We have a lot to clean up."

Said that he "always gets nervous" about the first game of the year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on the slow defensive start: "We are integrating new guys, learning new defensive principles. It's not an excuse by any means, but we've had a lot of disruption with injury. We're still getting guys back and figuring out rotations. The new guys learning what's expected."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on his message tonight: "We've got to grind it out. We struggled early last year, but we found ways to win. That what was most encouraging. I said, 'It's a 20-minute fight. Let's roll our sleeves up.'"

Name: Inside NU
Content: More: "I just thought we slowed the game down. I thought we got it more possession-by-possession."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on the defensive adjustments made: "Couple things. First and foremost, get back in transition. I thought in the first half, they really had us on our heels. I thought we slowed them down. I thought we got better in our gap help; we weren't as spread out."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins: "Winning is hard. That's how it is in college basketball. Everybody has good players."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins said that Martinelli was on a "pitch count" after a foot injury.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins said that Buie and Barnhizer were "fantastic," stressing Barnhizer's ability to get to the line.

Also said he was "really impressed" with Preston and Clayton.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins: "We're a work-in-progress. We're not nearly where we need to be yet, but you hopefully can learn lessons by winning games."

Said the second half featured "playing like we can play defensively."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins says the team was in a "dogfight." Also wished Binghamton's coach well in light of a family emergency.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins' opening statement: "Certainly elated that we won the game tonight. I knew this was going to be a difficult challenge, watching them on film. You play teams like this, they play very freely in these games. They come in, they really don't have a whole lot to lose."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chris Collins set to speak to the media shortly.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lots to improve upon, but 1-0 is always nice.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: Northwestern 72, Binghamton 61 

The Wildcats come away 1-0 despite trailing at halftime. The team's defense was steadily improved in the second period. 

Boo Buie contributed 27, while Brooks Barnhizer had 18 and 13 rebounds. Ryan Langborg added 13 points in his debut.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 72-61 after two good shots from Barnhizer.

Name: Inside NU
Content: An easy miss for the Bearcats causes another foul on Binghamton, and this one is looking like it's over.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie goes 1-for-2, and it's a nine-point lead for the purple and white.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer collects his fourth (!) steal of the night, and the Bearcats are running out of steam.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Both are made by Barnhizer. 69-61 Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer is whacked after a save by Clayton on an errant pass by Langborg. He'll head to the stripe with 48.4 seconds left, and Benson has fouled out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Benson sinks a floater to make it 67-61.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two more free throws for Buie, who now has 26. 67-59 'Cats, and a whole lot more breathing room.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Bearcats lose the handle, and the crowd is feeling it with NU up by six and two minutes to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie resets, drives and finishes over the defender. Strong work by No. 0, who's up to 24 on the night.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Bearcats just won't go away quite yet. Harried buries a three to make it a four-point game with 2:31 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie hits two free throws, and the Wildcats have a seven-point lead at 63-56.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Substitution watch: Clayton in for Berry with 2:56 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins utilizes another TO subsequent to a trey from Chenery. Suddenly, both sides have found it from deep.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Give Buie space at your own risk. He answers right back and is up to 20 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Dan Petcash hits a three to cut the lead to five. 3:35 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg drops it off perfectly to Barnhizer, who converts. Eight-point lead for the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins calls timeout, as the 'Cats haven't scored a field goal in 5:14 of play. Still, they hold a 56-50 lead with 4:17 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer up to 12 points and 12 rebounds, so we have our first double-double of the year.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 56-50 following the second Barnhizer make.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Binghamton calls timeout after the first make from Barnhizer. 55-50 lead for the 'Cats with 5:45 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Following a steal by Nicholson, it'll be another trip to the stripe for Barnhizer. Harried was incredulous of the call.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer hits both, and is up to 10 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer will head to the line after getting fouled.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Walker makes one of two shots. 52-50 Wildcats with 6:38 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A shove by Langborg puts Binghamton in the bonus.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Now, Buie picks up his fourth foul. Clayton will come in for No. 0.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie called for an offensive foul. He's gone cold in the second half, and now has three fouls.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
It's 52-49 'Cats at the under-8.

Buie has 17, while Langborg has chipped in 13. Two misses from the Princeton transfer in space have kept this one close, but Northwestern is at least on the right side of the scoreboard.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer draws a charge. Northwestern's defense has looked significantly sharper in the second half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Strong finish at the cup by Chenery cuts the NU advantage to three with 8:38 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Clayton assessed for his third foul, so he'll check out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg has gotten white hot, hitting a jumper off the inbound. Northwestern now leads 52-47.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
We're in official review after the ball clanked off Barnhizer.

Binghamton hasn't scored in 3:04 of play, giving NU momentum that it's finally seized.

Langborg and Preston have combined for 17 points, seven rebounds, three blocks and a steal. Good beginning at Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie slow to get up after an awkward foul. Clayton coming in for him with 10:02 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie goes strong for a layup after Torrence lost the handle. The lid has come off this place, with the stress temporarily relieved.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg sinks a turnaround J, and the Wildcats *finally* have the lead! The crowd is jumping at WRA.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston with a huge swat! He's putting together a strong debut.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie throws it away off the inbound, over the head of Langborg.

That kind of evening for the Wildcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Preston forces a steal, and Benson is called for the take foul.

Should've counted the flip-in off the glass, imo

Name: Inside NU
Content:
At the under-12, it's 47-46 Binghamton.

Preston has poured in the last four points for NU, but the 'Cats still haven't gotten over the hump. They're running out of time to do so.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Benson converts a tough fadeaway jumper, but Preston slams down a lob from Buie. It's 47-46 Binghamton.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer is 3-for-9 and has missed multiple times close to the rim. Not an ideal start.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Preston cleans up a Clayton miss to make it 45-44.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg has checked back in, which is good news on the injury front.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Off a tremendous cut through white defenders, Chenery finishes at the rim to augment the lead back to three. We're inside of 15 minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Buie makes one of two.

Incredibly, the Wildcats still can't find a way to take the lead.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie starts and stops to draw a foul. No. 0 will head to the line with an opportunity to tie the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Seeing this Culver's promo is a great reminder that there needs to be one on campus

Name: Inside NU
Content:
At the under-16, it's 43-41 Binghamton.

Only four made baskets so far in the second half. Wildcats still haven't led since it was 14-13.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer commits a questionable foul, and neither Collins nor the student section are pleased.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Torrence finishes high off the glass to retain the Binghamton lead. He's up to 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Clayton subs in for Langborg, who seemed to be limping off.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg follows up a missed Buie three, and the 'Cats have tied it up at 41-41.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After four misses, Berry finally converts from deep. 41-39 now.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg misses an open corner three, and Torrence fights through two defenders to lay it in. 41-36 Bearcats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson misses both, but Berry exercises good effort to force a jump ball and keep the rock with NU.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson pokes the ball away and is fouled on the other end on an alley-oop try, so No. 34 will head to the line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson already up to three blocks after a rejection.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Binghamton inbounds, and the second half has begun.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Notably, Ty Berry has played just six minutes so far.

He has two fouls and is 0-for-3 shooting.

Not the first 20 minutes he expected.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALF: Binghamton 39, Northwestern 36

Not the first half that anyone envisioned, to say the least.

Boo Buie has 14 points on 6-of-12 shooting, while Brooks Barnhizer and Ryan Langborg have posted eight and seven, respectively.

Binghamton has five players with 6+ points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie sinks a turnaround floater inside of 10 seconds left, but Binghamton gets a second-chance bucket to go before the buzzer.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nicholson finishes in the post after an assist by Buie. 1:16 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Nehemiah Benson hangs tough for a jumper over Buie. Five-point lead for the Bearcats inside of two minutes left in the first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie tries a spin but gets emphatically rejected by Chenery, who added a staredown. Still 35-32 Binghamton.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Heads up play by Nicholson to throw it off the Binghamton defender following a Berry miss.

At the under-4 timeout, Binghamton still leads 35-32. The Wildcats have already turned it over seven times, and haven't led since it was 14-13.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After a Chenery jumper, Langborg throws it away. Collins holds his arms up in frustration.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer converts both. The junior is up to eight points on the night, and the lead is just one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer nets a filthy swat and draws contact going coast-to-coast. He'll shoot two and has a chance to make it a one-point affair.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Buie patiently works his way to the basket to make it 33-30 Binghamton. He's up to 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg starting to feel it! He swishes a deep trey after crossing over his defender. It's 31-28 Binghamton.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Langborg pulls up from the corner of the paint, but Harried cuts through the defense to keep the lead at six.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Binghamton loses the handle, and that takes us to the under-8. It's 29-23 Bearcats over Wildcats.

Buie has 10 for NU, and Barnhizer has added six. But, nobody else has exceeded more than three points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer lays it in on the jelly, and Buie hits from deep to make it a six-point game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Petcash adds two more FTs. Back to an 11-point lead for Binghamton.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Binghamton in the bonus with 8:49 left in the half.

Yikes!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Subsequent to a Nicholson block, Barnhizer works his way down low for two. 27-18 Binghamton.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Binghamton hits two more from the stipe, and Nicholson is assessed for a travel.

Yeah.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern basketball thus far

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The Bearcats swing it around in the far corner, and Petcash buries a three.

The lead has ballooned to nine for the visitors.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 22-16 Binghamton after two free throws are good by Tymu Chenery. To make matters worse, Buie lost the handle on a feed.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Barnhizer misses on one end, and Clayton is whistled for his second foul on the other. Now seven fouls for the 'Cats, and we've yet to hit 10 minutes of play.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With one on the clock, Torrence banks in a wild three. He's up to eight points for the Bearcats.
